Make sure you wash your hands well
We all know that they need to be washed (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you need to do it in the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30–40 seconds for the washing to remove sufficiently dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands
And most of us wash them shorter!
Just warm water and ordinary soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even reject it).
When washing, we rub not only the bottoms and tops of the hands, but also: fingertips (joined or individually) – rub them with circular movements on the inside of the other hand, spaces between the fingers (split the hands, rubbing the fingers against each other), thumbs – each thumb we embrace the other hand and in such an embrace we turn it for a while to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when it is not possible to wash hands) we should wipe hands with a wet cloth, and then use antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from 5 zł).
When using the public toilet, do not touch handles or doors with washed hands (recommendation of the Main Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open them with a paper towel.
Iranian President says he has rejected a proposal for talks with the US, Donald Trump denies
Tehran did not enter into talks with the American side during the UN General Assembly in New York, despite an offer by the Americans to lift the sanctions – Iranian President Hasan Rowhani declared on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump said that the Iranian side had requested the lifting of the restrictions, which he did not agree to.
According to Iranian President Hassan Rouhani, the Americans proposed to lift all sanctions on Tehran in exchange for negotiating a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran's nuclear programme and its ballistic missile programme.
Rowhani: Iran will not engage in talks under maximum pressure
The Iranian President stated that he did not agree to the talks because of the "toxic atmosphere".
He stated that he had met with American diplomats because he had been persuaded by France, Germany and the United Kingdom.
However, he stressed that Iran would not enter into talks in an atmosphere of "maximum pressure".
"Even if we want to negotiate with the Americans in the 5+1 format, no one can predict what the final outcome will be," Rowhani said.
The day before, the Iranian leader had said that he was not excluding talks with the US, and he had accused the European parties of favouring US sanctions on Iran.
He added that sanctions imposed on Iran after the US withdrawal from the nuclear deal "are a precondition that does not allow" for dialogue.
If we manage to lift this precondition and if America lifts sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America," he declared.
He added that he would not rule out meeting with US President Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a talk during the UN General Assembly last week.
Trump: “Iran asked, I said no”
Donald Trump wrote on Twitter that he rejected the Iranian side's request.
"Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions on them so that we could meet.
Of course I said 'no!' tweeted the US President.
Nuclear tension in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease tensions between Washington and Tehran in order to somehow rescue the 2015 agreement with Iran to which they were signatories.
In exchange for the lifting of economic sanctions, Iran would abandon its nuclear weapons programme and place the nuclear sector under the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the United States withdrew from the agreement in May 2015, the remaining signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to keep the agreement in force.
So far, none of this has worked.
Washington is using maximum pressure tactics on Iran, and sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has announced that if it does not receive a permit to export the raw material, it will limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
