The power of Oławy jumps.
The title of the report from the amateur sports competitions, held on Sunday afternoon 15 September at the hippodrome at Oleandry Street in Oława, may be misleading for some.
Real power is a long way away, but that is the name of one of the types of horse racing...
The competition of jumping power consists in overcoming by rider and horse ever higher obstacles, which in the most prestigious international competitions exceed even two meters.
It is worth adding here that the long-term and still unbeaten world record, established in 1949, by the Chilean Albert Larraguibel, on horse "Huaso", is 247 cm.
Of course, nobody jumped so high in Oława, but the result of the best local amazons at the level of 135 cm is not the worst either...
The competition organized by tireless Jan Sienkiewicz and other activists of JKS "W siodle" was a demonstration part of the slightly earlier held there "Tęczowe zawodów ejazdeckich", about which we write more extensively in this issue of the newspaper, on page 22.
Eight amateur riders trained in the Oławski JKS.
Four competed on ponies and four on large horses.
In the first group Nikola Szołdra performed best, reaching the crazy "Sprinter".
This small, but very dynamic rumak started from overcoming obstacles spread out at a height of 40 cm, and ended only at the station with the top beam 125 cm away from the ground.
However, he was unsuccessful, and after three consecutive rejections, he was removed from the competition by the jury.
The second place in the jumps of ponies was taken by Amelia Pawlak, reaching "Famy", and the third Lena Boruń on "Harmider".
The youngest participant of the tournament - Inga Aksman, galloping and jumping through obstacles on the small mare "Carmen" competed ambitiously.
Even greater emotions accompanied the starting amateurs and spectators during the competition with the participation of large horses.
The threatening-looking falls included Paulina Szewczyk, reaching the "Declaration", and Anastazja Abramenko, who was riding the "Flight".
Fortunately, apart from minor bruises, neither the amazons nor the horses were hurt, so they continued to participate in the competition.
Weronika Łuczkiewicz had a lot of problems with introducing the young mare “Wineta” to the park.
We needed either a trainer's assistant, or another horse for the pair, behind which there was a little crazy "Wineta".
After counting the obstacles from the parking lot, she also skied the full length, so for a few moments in the pits and on the accelerator it was getting dangerous. “Everything is under control!”, Jan Sienkiewicz calmed down a little bit the frightened spectators, especially the youngest ones.
Since the beginning of the competition for large horses, Marta Masalska has performed well in the parking lot, finishing the beautifully presented “Whisky”.
This dignified mare, together with an experienced amateur, after the second approach in the final stage was the first to jump 135 cm and it was the best result of the competition at that moment.
After a while, however, Paulina Szewczyk on "Deklaracja", Weronika Łuczkiewicz on "Wineta" and Anastazja Abramenko on "Lotka" also counted the same height.
To decorate the flo and after receiving the prizes in the form of equestrian equipment, all these competitors went out together, and at the end together with the amateurs on ponies in Radecki's march performed an impressive honorary round, ending these interesting and exciting competitions.
