It regulates which flights have HEAD status and who can be on board government aircraft with the most important persons in the country.
The Act also specifies who is responsible for maintaining the Central Flight Register.
55 senators voted in favour of the bill, 12 against, and four abstained.
According to the law, every flight of the president will be a flight "executed in an official mission".
